content:
To upload files in an OmniScript, add a File input element or an Image input element. Details about uploads are added to the Files node of the OmniScript's Data JSON.

Files are uploaded to Salesforce Content Documents directly by default. To associate with a Salesforce object, specify the object Ids in the Content Parent Id field.

To run a Vlocity Open Interface after upload, set the Remote Action section's Remote Class and Remote Method fields. The specified method receives a Map<String, Object> list containing the File data from the Data JSON.

File elements accept up to 2GB file size by default. OmniScripts and FlexCards support all image file types. If set, the lightning-file-upload attribute filters file types in the user's file browser.

Add a File or Image element to enable upload functionality. File elements accept up to 2GB file size by default.
title: Uploading Files and Images in OmniScripts
